<subSubSection pageNumber="777" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="777">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="777">Note:</emphasis>
This and the slightly earlier 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1759)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Rondeletia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="777">Rondeletia repens</emphasis>
L. (1759)
</taxonomicName>
share some original elements in common, which has led some authors (e.g. Steyermark in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="777">Mem. New York Bot. Gard.</emphasis>
23: 395. 1972) to treat 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="777">P. repens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new combination. However, there are some discrepancies between the two and they appear to be best treated as independent names.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
